treader.com/2008/06/02/book-awards/chopin-wins-the-audie/ |accessdate=22 May 2019 |work=BookListReader.com |publisher=BookList Publications, a division of the ALA |date=June 2, 2008}}</ref>: '''''[[The Chopin Manuscript]]: A Serial Thriller''''' by [[Lee Child]], David Corbett, [[Joseph Finder]], Jim Fusilli, John Gilstrap, [[James Grady]], [[David Hewson]], [[P.J. Parrish]], and [[Jeffery Deaver]]. Narrated by Alfred Molina. \n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\">{{cite news |title=Best Audiobook Titles of the Year Honored in New York |url=http://independentpublisher.com/article.php?page=1163 |accessdate=22 May 2019 |work=IndependentPublisher.com |publisher=Jenkins Group, Inc.}}</ref>: '''''Inspired By...[[The Bible Experience]] (New Testament)''''' by Media Group. Narrated by Angela Bassett, Cuba Gooding, Jr., Samuel L. Jackson, Blair Underwood, Denzel Washington, et al. \n|2006<ref name=\"LCLAudies\">{{cite web |title=Audie Awards |url=https://lincolnlibraries.org/bookguide/award-winners/audie-awards/ |website=LincolnLibraries.org |publisher=Lincoln City Libraries [NE] |accessdate=23 May 2019}}</ref>: '''''The Hitchhiker\u2019s Guide to the Galaxy: Tertiary Phase''''' by Douglas Adams. Narrated by Simon Jones, Geoffrey McGivern, and a full cast.\n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''''My Life''''' written and narrated by [[Bill Clinton]]. \n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''''[[Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix]]''''' by [[J.K. Rowling]]. Narrated by [[Jim Dale]]. }}\n'''''2004: inaugural'''''\n|-\n|'''Original Work'''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\"></ref>: ''Spin'' by [[Edelman and Fishman|Harvey Edelman and Neil Fishman]], adapted for audio by David B. Coe. Narrated by [[Jim Dale]], Barrett Leddy, Lisa Livesay, Nicola Barber, Khristine Hvam, Nick Sullivan, John Brady, and Johnny Heller.\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: ''Romeo and Juliet: A Novel'' by [[David Hewson]]. Narrated by [[Richard Armitage (actor)|Richard Armitage]]. \n|201