a Spencer]], and [[Bahni Turpin]]<ref name=\"BahniNHF\"></ref>. \n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: ''[[Duma Key]]'' by [[Stephen King]]. Narrated by [[John Slattery]]. \n|2008<ref name=\"Audible2008B\"></ref>: ''Tallgrass''<ref name=\"LK2008\"></ref> by [[Sandra Dallas]]. Narrated by Lorelei King<ref name=\"LK2008\"></ref>. }}\n'''''Prior to 2008, this award category was titled \"Fiction, Unabridged\"'''''\n{{bulleted list\n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref>: ''Rise and Shine'' by [[Anna Quindlen]]. Narrated by Carol Monda. \n|2006<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''A Slight Trick of the Mind'' by Mitch Cullin. Narrated by Simon Jones.\n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''The Darling'' by Russell Banks. Narrated by Mary Beth Hurt.\n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[All Over Creation]]'' by [[Ruth Ozeki]]. Narrated by [[Kate Fleming|Anna Fields]].\n|2003<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Middlesex (novel)|Middlesex]]'' by [[Jeffrey Eugenides]]. Narrated by [[Kristoffer Tabori]].\n|2002<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[The Talisman (King and Straub novel)|The Talisman]]'' by [[Stephen King]] and [[Peter Straub]]. Narrated by [[Frank Muller]]. \n|2001<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Fierce Invalids Home from Hot Climates]]'' by [[Tom Robbins]]. Narrated by [[Keith Szarabajka]]. }}\n|-\n|'''Literary Fiction'''\n\n'''/ Classics'''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\"></ref>: ''[[Bleak House]]'' by [[Charles Dickens]]. Narrated by [[Miriam Margolyes]].\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: ''House of Names'' by [[Colm T\u00f3ib\u00edn|Colm Toibin]]. Narrated by [[Juliet Stevenson]], et al. \n|2017<ref name=\"Seventeen\"></ref>: ''[[Homegoing (Gyasi novel)|Homegoing]]'' by [[Yaa Gyasi]]. Narrated by Dominic Hoffman. \n|2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\"></ref>: ''Little Big Man'' by [[Thomas Berger (novelist)|Thomas Berger]]. Narrated by Scott Sowers, cameo by David Aaron Baker. }}\n'''''2015: See separate defunct categories \"Literary Fiction\" and \"Classics\" for winners prior to 2016''''' \n|-\n|'''Mystery'''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\"></ref>: ''The Punishment She Deserves'' by [[Elizabeth George]]. Narrated by [[Simon Vance]].\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: ''[[The Girl Who Takes an Eye for an Eye]]'' by [[David Lagercrantz]]. Narrated by [[Simon Vance]]. \n|2017<ref name=\"Seventeen\"></ref>: ''The Crossing'' by [[Michael Connelly]]. Narrated by [[Titus Welliver]]. \n|2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\"></ref>: ''[[Career of Evil]]'' by [[J. K. Rowling|Robert Galbraith]]. Narrated by [[Robert Glenister]]. \n|2015<ref name=\"Fifteen\"></ref>: ''[[The Silkworm]] '' by [[J. K. Rowling|Robert Galbraith]]. Narrated by [[Robert Glenister]]. \n|2014<ref name=\"Fourteen\"></ref>: ''Unleashed: Andy Carpenter, Book 11'' by [[David Rosenfelt]]. Narrated by [[Grover Gardner]]. \n|2013<ref name=\"BLR2013\"></ref>: ''The Beautiful Mystery: A [[Chief Inspector Armand Gamache|Chief Inspector Gamache]] Novel'' by [[Louise Penny]]. Narrated by [[Ralph Cosham]]. \n|2012<ref name=\"BLR2012\"></ref><ref name=\"Twelve\"></ref>: ''Feast Day of Fools: A Novel'' by [[James Lee Burke]]. Narrated by [[Will Patton]]. \n|2011<ref name=\"BookListReader2011\"></ref>: ''[[The Reversal]]: A [[The Lincoln Lawyer|Lincoln Lawyer]] Novel'' by [[Michael Connelly]]. Narrated by Peter Giles. \n|2010<ref name=\"BLR2010\"></ref>: ''[[Devil in a Blue Dress]]: An [[Ezekiel \"Easy\" Rawlins|Easy Rawlins]] Mystery'' by [[Walter Mosley]]. Narrated by Michael Boatman.\n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: ''[[Voice of the Violin]]: An [[Salvo_Montalbano#Novels|Inspector Montalbano]] Mystery'' by [[Andrea Camilleri]]. Narrated by [[Grover Gardner]].\n|2008<ref name=\"Audible2008B\"></ref>: ''[[The Tin Roof Blowdown]]: A [[Dave Robicheaux]] Novel'' by [[James Lee Burke]]. Narrated by Will Patton.\n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref>: ''[[Echo Park (novel)|Echo Park]]: [[Harry Bosch]] Series, Book 12'' by [[Michael Connelly]]. Narrated by [[Len Cari