ok)|David and Goliath]]: Underdogs, Misfits, and the Art of Battling Giants'' written and narrated by [[Malcolm Gladwell]]. \n|2013<ref name=\"BLR2013\"></ref>: ''Breasts: A Natural and Unnatural History'' by [[Florence Williams]]. Narrated by [[Kate Reading]]. \n|2012<ref name=\"BLR2012\"></ref><ref name=\"Twelve\"></ref>: ''The Murder of the Century: The Gilded Age Crime That Scandalized a City and Sparked the Tabloid Wars '' by [[Paul Collins (American writer)|Paul Collins]]. Narrated by [[William Dufris]]. \n|2011<ref name=\"BookListReader2011\"></ref>: ''[[The Immortal Life of Henrietta Lacks]]''<ref name=\"BahniNHF\"></ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Reviews: The Immortal Life of Henrietta Lacks |url=https://www.audiofilemagazine.com/reviews/read/53884/ |website=AudioFileMagazine.com |publisher=AudioFile Publications, Inc. |accessdate=17 May 2019}}</ref> by [[Rebecca Skloot]]. Narrated by Cassandra Campbell with [[Bahni Turpin]].\n|2010<ref name=\"BLR2010\"></ref>: ''The National Parks: America\u2019s Best Idea'' written and narrated by [[Ken Burns]] and [[Dayton Duncan]]. \n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: ''[[Hot, Flat, and Crowded]]: Why We Need a Green Revolution\u2014and How It Can Renew America'' by [[Thomas Friedman|Thomas L. Friedman]]. Narrated by [[Oliver Wyman (actor)|Oliver Wyman]].\n|2008<ref name=\"LOL2008\"></ref><ref name=\"Audible2008B\"></ref>: ''[[Roots: The Saga of an American Family]]'' by [[Alex Haley]]. Narrated by [[Avery Brooks]]. }}\n'''''Prior to 2008, this award category was titled \"Non-Fiction, Unabridged\"'''''\n{{bulleted list\n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref>: ''Narrow Dog to Carcassonne'' by [[Terry Darlington]]. Narrated by Steve Hodson.\n|2006<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[The World is Flat]]: A Brief History of the Twenty-First Century'' by [[Thomas L. Friedman]]. Narrated by [[Oliver Wyman (actor)|Oliver Wyman]].\n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[The Island at the Center of the World]]: The Epic Story Of Dutch 